  "text": "Firefox NSS TLS/SSL Implementation Audit\n\nThis audit identified five core TLS/SSL protocol implementation files in the Mozilla Firefox Network Security Services (NSS) library:\n\n1. mozilla-firefox/firefox:security/nss/lib/ssl/ssl3con.c\n   - Implements SSL 3.0 and TLS record processing with cipher suite negotiation\n   - Primary protocol functions: ssl3_HandleClientHello, ssl3_HandleServerHello, ssl3_ComputeMasterSecret, ssl3_DeriveConnectionKeys\n   - Manages pre-TLS 1.3 handshake flows and symmetric key derivation from pre-master secrets\n\n2. mozilla-firefox/firefox:security/nss/lib/ssl/tls13con.c\n   - Implements TLS 1.3 handshake and record processing with modern cryptographic key derivation\n   - Primary protocol functions: tls13_SetCipherSpec, tls13_ComputeHandshakeSecrets, tls13_HandleClientHelloPart2, tls13_HandleServerHelloPart2\n   - Handles HelloRetryRequest, encrypted extensions, certificate messages, and HKDF-based secret derivation\n\n3. mozilla-firefox/firefox:security/nss/lib/ssl/dtlscon.c\n   - Implements DTLS (Datagram TLS) protocol-specific handling for unreliable UDP transports\n   - Primary protocol functions: dtls_HandleHandshake, dtls_TLSVersionToDTLSVersion, dtls_DTLSVersionToTLSVersion\n   - Manages retransmission timers, message queueing, and DTLS version mapping from TLS versions\n\n4. mozilla-firefox/firefox:security/nss/lib/ssl/ssl3ecc.c\n   - Implements elliptic curve cryptography (ECC) operations for ECC cipher suites\n   - Primary protocol functions: ssl_NamedGroup2ECParams, ssl_ECPubKey2NamedGroup, ssl_CreateECDHEphemeralKeyPair, ssl_GetECGroupWithStrength\n   - Handles ECC key generation, parameter conversion, and ECDHE ephemeral key pair creation\n\n5. mozilla-firefox/firefox:security/nss/lib/ssl/sslexp.h\n   - Header file declaring experimental SSL APIs not guaranteed to remain available in future NSS versions\n   - Primary exported APIs: SSL_GetExtensionSupport, SSL_InstallExtensionHooks, SSL_EXPERIMENTAL_API macro\n   - Provides extension support queries and custom TLS extension hook installation for advanced applications\n\nAll files are located in the mozilla-firefox/firefox repository under security/nss/lib/ssl/ and represent critical components of NSS's TLS protocol implementation."
}

